**COMPLETE PROCESS ENGINEERING DESIGN: EFB & DECANTER CAKE PRE-TREATMENT
FACILITY WITH PKSA TREATMENT**

**60 TPH FFB Palm Oil Mill**\
**Location:** Bogor, West Java, Indonesia\
**Date:** March 3, 2026\
**Design Basis:** 24/7 Continuous Operation

**EXECUTIVE SUMMARY**

This document provides complete process engineering specifications for a
dual-stream facility processing **Empty Fruit Bunches (EFB)** and
**Decanter Cake (DC)** from a 60 TPH FFB palm oil mill, including
innovative **Palm Kernel Shell Ash (PKSA)** alkaline pre-treatment. The
facility achieves:

-   **Stage 1:** Mechanical size reduction to D90 ≤2mm and moisture
    control (45-55% MC)

-   **Stage 2:** Chemical pre-treatment using PKSA for 30-35% lignin
    reduction in 1.5-2 hours

-   **Final product:** Biology-ready substrate for microbes and BSF
    larvae at pH 6.5-8.0

**Key Performance Metrics:**

-   **Throughput:** 331 t FW EFB/day + 50-80 t FW DC/day

-   **PKSA dose:** 6-10 kg/t FW EFB (FREE - mill waste stream)

-   **Total processing time:** 18-24 hours from truck arrival to
    biology-ready substrate

-   **CAPEX:** \$540K-\$980K (Stages 1+2 combined)

-   **Footprint:** 1,800 m² (1,400 m² Stage 2 + 400 m² Stage 1 shared
    equipment)

