│  → PR-01 Screw Press (70→47% MC)       → DC-PRESS-01 (85→60% MC)          │``
│  → BC-05 → SD-01 Shredder              → BC-12 (pressed cake)              │``
│  → BC-06 → HM-01 Hammer Mill           → Optional: SD-02 Light shredding   │``
│  → BC-07 → VS-01 Screen (2mm)          → BC-13 to Stage 2                  │``
│  → BC-08 Recycle loop                                                       │``
│  → BC-09 → Buffer Bin (20m³)                                                │``
│                                                                             │``
│  OUTPUT: 331 t/day EFB at 2mm, 47% MC  OUTPUT: 50-80 t/day DC at 60% MC   │``
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘``
                    ↓                                    ↓``
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐``
│                    STAGE 2: PKSA CHEMICAL PRE-TREATMENT                     │``
│                         (EFB and DC processed separately)                   │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 1: Mixer Loading (10 min)                                            │``
│  - Screw feeder drops 165.6t EFB OR 80t DC into paddle mixer drum         │``
│  - Add water 1:1 ratio (165.6t for EFB, 80t for DC)                       │``
│  - Total slurry: 331t EFB batch OR 160t DC batch                          │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 2: PKSA Dosing (2 min)                                               │``
│  - Pump PKSA slurry (10% concentration) from 20m³ tank                    │``
│  - EFB dose: 1.6t dry PKSA (16t slurry) = 6-10 kg/t FW                   │``
│  - DC dose: 0.8t dry PKSA (8t slurry) = 10-12 kg/t FW                    │``
│  - pH rises instantly to 10-12 (K₂O + CaO → KOH + Ca(OH)₂)               │``
``│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 3: Reaction (60-90 min) - THE CRITICAL CHEMICAL STEP                │``
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │``
│  │  PADDLE MIXER DRUM PMD-01 - 6m diameter × 6m length                 │  │``
│  │  - 10 RPM rotation with 40 paddle blades                             │  │``
│  │  - Carbon steel with 8mm EPDM rubber lining (alkali-resistant)     │  │``
│  │  - 2 parallel shafts with stainless steel 304 paddles               │  │``
│  │                                                                       │  │``
│  │  WHAT HAPPENS INSIDE:                                                 │  │``
│  │  • KOH cleaves ester bonds in lignin-carbohydrate complexes (LCC)   │  │``
│  │  • Lignin fragments dissolve into aqueous phase (8-10 g/L)          │  │``
│  │  • Cellulose fibrils swell and separate (surface area ↑ 3-4×)       │  │``
│  │  • Hemicellulose saponification releases fermentable sugars          │  │``
│  │                                                                       │  │``
│  │  KINETICS (2mm particles, 28-35°C ambient):                          │  │``
│  │  - 30 min: 18-22% lignin reduction                                   │  │``
│  │  - 60 min: 28-32% lignin reduction ← OPTIMAL                         │  │``
│  │  - 90 min: 30-35% lignin reduction (diminishing returns)            │  │``
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 4: Drain (5 min)                                                      │``
│  - Bottom valve opens → 150m³ spent liquor drains through 5mm mesh        │``
│  - Liquor (pH 11, 8-10 g/L dissolved lignin) → POME pond                 │``
│  - Wet EFB/DC (70% MC, pH 10-12) drops onto conveyor                      │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 5: Re-Press (60 min)                                                  │``
│  - CB-15TC screw press squeezes 70% → 50-55% MC                           │``
│  - Press cake (165t at 50-55% MC, pH 10-12) to neutralization bay        │``
│  - Recovered liquor (25m³) → POME pond for reuse                          │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 6-8: Neutralization (24 hours total)                                 │``
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │``
│  │  NEUTRALIZATION BAY #1 (12m×12m×1.5m high)                           │  │``
│  │  Phase 1 (0-12 hours): Passive CO₂ carbonation                       │  │``
│  │  - Front-end loader spreads 165t into windrow (1.0-1.5m height)     │  │``
│  │  - Atmospheric CO₂ (0.04%) dissolves into alkaline moisture:         │  │``
│  │    • KOH + CO₂ → KHCO₃ (potassium bicarbonate)                       │  │``
│  │    • Ca(OH)₂ + CO₂ → ``CaCO``₃ + H₂O (limestone formation)              │  │``
│  │  - pH drops from 10-12 → 8 over 12 hours                             │  │``
│  │  - Slight exotherm: Temperature rises 5-10°C from carbonation        │  │``
│  │                                                                       │  │``
│  │  POME Spray + Turn (30 min)                                           │  │``
``│  │  - Spray 82m³ diluted POME (1:1 water, pH 4.5-5.5)                  │  │``
│  │  - Bobcat turns windrow 2-3 passes with hydraulic turner            │  │``
│  │  - POME acidity + residual alkalinity → pH 7-7.5                    │  │``
│  │  - Nutrient loading: C:N improves from 60:1 → 35:1                  │  │``
│  │                                                                       │  │``
│  │  Phase 2 (12-24 hours): Final cure                                    │  │``
│  │  - Continue passive carbonation → pH stabilizes at 6.5-8.0          │  │``
│  │  - Temperature check: Must be <45°C before biology                   │  │``
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 9: Biology GO Check (15 min) - CRITICAL QUALITY GATE                │``
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐             │``
│  │  Handheld measurements (MANDATORY pass before Stage 3):  │             │``
│  │  ✓ pH: 6.5-8.0 (pH meter)                                │             │``
│  │  ✓ Temperature: <45°C (IR thermometer)                   │             │``
│  │  ✓ Visual: Fluffy, no clumps, uniform color             │             │``
│  │                                                           │             │``
│  │  IF ANY PARAMETER FAILS → Hold 6 hours, recheck         │             │``
│  │  Alkaline (pH>8) or hot (>45°C) material will KILL      │             │``
│  │  microbes and BSF larvae instantly.                      │             │``
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘             │``
│                                                                             │``
│  STEP 10: OPDC Blending (60 min)                                           │``
│  - Bobcat mixes treated EFB (60% DM) + treated DC (40% DM)                │``
│  - Final substrate: pH 7.0-8.5, C:N 30-35:1, 55% MC                       │``
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘``
                              ↓``
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐``
│                   FINAL OUTPUT: BIOLOGY-READY SUBSTRATE                     │``
│                                                                             │``
│  Specifications:                                                            │``
│  • Particle size: D90 ≤2mm (EFB), paste-like (DC)                         │``
│  • Moisture: 55% MC                                                         │``
│  • pH: 6.5-8.0 (safe for biology)                                          │``
│  • Temperature: <45°C (enzymes/microbes viable)                            │``
│  • Lignin reduction: 30-35% (BSF-ready)                                    │``
│  • C:N ratio: 30-35:1 (optimal for bioconversion)                         │``
│  • Throughput: 331 t/day ready for Stage 3 Microbes or Stage 4 BSF        │``
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘``
