**WHAT DOES IT DO:**

Removes **abrasive contaminants** (sand, gravel, small stones) from raw
EFB **before** mechanical pressing and milling. This prevents:

-   Premature wear of screw press flights (AR400 steel still wears with
    silica)

-   Bearing damage in shredder and hammer mill

-   Screen mesh blinding in final classification

**HOW IT WORKS:**

1.  **Material Entry:** EFB bunches (100-300mm) tumble into rotating
    drum from BC-01 conveyor

2.  **Rotation + Vibration:** Drum rotates at 10-15 RPM while eccentric
    weights create vibratory motion

3.  **Size Separation:**

    -   **Undersize (\<20mm):** Sand, gravel, dirt, small fiber
        fragments fall through 20mm round perforations → collection
        hopper

    -   **Oversize (\>20mm):** EFB bunches, fiber clumps retained in
        drum → tumble forward to discharge end

4.  **Discharge:** Clean EFB exits discharge end, drops onto BC-02
    conveyor

5.  **Fines Collection:** Undersize fines (1-3% of input mass, ≈400
    kg/day) collect in 2m³ bin → manual wheelbarrow emptying daily to
    compost yard

**MACHINE SITS ON:**

-   **Structural steel frame:** Welded 150mm×150mm box section steel,
    bolted to concrete pad

-   **Foundation:** Reinforced concrete pad 8m L × 3m W × 0.4m thick
    (150mm rebar grid), compacted gravel base

-   **Vibration isolation:** 8× rubber isolation pads (200mm dia × 50mm
    thick) under frame legs to prevent vibration transmission to
    building structure

**OUTPUT OF MACHINE:**

-   **Product:** Clean EFB bunches at 65-70% MC, free of
    sand/gravel/stones (98% removal efficiency)

-   **Mass flow:** 13.5 t/hr (18 t/hr design) - slightly reduced from
    input (13.8 t/hr) due to fines removal

-   **State:** Still whole/partially broken bunches, 100-300mm size,
    ready for dewatering

**OPERATOR SAFETY & MAINTENANCE:**

-   **Guards:** Full sheet metal enclosure with interlocked inspection
    doors (door open → trommel stops)

-   **Noise:** 85-90 dBA at 1m - hearing protection recommended

-   **Dust:** Water mist spray at feed point (optional) to suppress dust

-   **Inspection:** Every 4 hours check for screen blinding (wet EFB can
    clog perforations) - water hose manual cleaning if needed

-   **Wear parts:** Screen panels (AR400 perforated plate) replace
    annually, cost \$800-\$1,500

